    "description": "FreeCharge Advisory Limited invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Financial Analyst at our Chennai location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout FreeCharge Advisory Limited:\nFreeCharge Advisory Limited is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in Income Tax\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in Bloomberg Terminal\n• Proficiency in Ind AS\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in Tally\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Learning & development budget\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with FreeCharge Advisory Limited!",
